    "description": "The strategy seeks to capture a recurring equity return anomaly around option expiration week by holding the S and P 100 ETF (OEF) only when the next listed U.S. option expiration falls within the coming five calendar days. The premise is that dealer hedging flows, index rebalancing, and expiration related positioning can create a short lived, systematic bias in the underlying index during expiration week, which can be harvested with a simple, rule based exposure toggle rather than trading options directly.\n\nPortfolio decisions are made weekly: every Monday at 10:00 local market time the system queries the exchange trading calendar for the next upcoming option expiration date, and if that expiration occurs within five days it enters a full allocation long position in OEF (target 100 percent notional). The position is held through the week and is fully exited on the actual expiration date via end of day liquidation logic. There is no shorting, no leverage beyond full notional allocation, and no explicit volatility, stop loss, or drawdown control; risk is primarily managed by limiting exposure to a narrow holding window and being otherwise in cash.",
